HEADWORD: Choledology
<hw>Chol`e*dol"o*gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>cholh`</grk> bile + <ets>-logy</ets>. Cf. F.
<ets>chol⟦eacute⟧dologie</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A treatise
on the bile and bilary organs.</def> <rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ Littr⟦eacute⟧ says that the word
<xex>chol⟦eacute⟧dologie</xex> is absolutely barbarous, there being no
Greek word <?/. A proper form would be <xex>cholology</xex>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

